The paper presents a system for autonomous aerial inspection using visual-inertial mapping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system also involves computer vision techniques for feature-based localization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The system also involves machine learning techniques for trajectory planning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The system also involves control systems for safe and efficient operation, which falls under the category of control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the system involves decision-making algorithms for autonomous operation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
